      <hedline>
        <hl1>Defending Napster To the Editor:</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Evan Kaiser letter on Aug 31 article holds music file-sharing technology will boost music industry; drawing</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>One need only look at the historical record to predict the effects of the music file-sharing technology. Remember audio tape? Videotape? Whenever consumers gain access to accurate means for the reproduction of works of art or entertainment, the market balloons because demand takes off, which overwhelms any negative effects of consumer ''theft.'' Will the entertainment industry ever learn?</p>
        <p>EVAN KAISER  Seekonk, Mass.</p>
      </block>
